# Architecture

## Current layout (monolith)

| Unit | Role |
|------|------|
| `src/wincher_mcp/server.py` | MCP server, Wincher HTTP client, all tools |
| `wincher_mcp_server.py` | Root shim for legacy MCP config paths |
| `pyproject.toml` | PyPI package `wincher-mcp`, console script |
| `requirements.txt` | Runtime deps (mirror of `pyproject.toml`) |
| `docs/SETUP.md`, `docs/EXAMPLES.md`, `docs/PYPI.md` | Setup, prompts, publishing |

Published on PyPI as **`wincher-mcp`**; local dev: `pip install -e ".[dev]"`.

## Data flow

```
Claude / Cursor  --stdio-->  MCP Server  --HTTPS Bearer-->  Wincher API (/v1/...)
```

- Production host: `PRODUCTION_BASE_URL` in code (`https://api.wincher.com`).
- Staging: enabled by MCP arg `--use-staging` (in `args`, not env). Host only from `WINCHER_STAGING_API_HOST`. Never hardcode or document the staging URL in this repo.
- TOON output: optional MCP arg `--use-toon`, or per-tool `output_format` (`text` | `toon`). Encodes capped API `data` via `python-toon` (`from toon import encode`).
- Auth: `WINCHER_API_KEY` via `_api_key()` on every request.
- HTTP: `wincher_request(method, endpoint)`; GET via `make_wincher_request()`.
- Errors: `_format_http_error()` reports endpoint path only (no request URL; avoids leaking staging host).

## Tool → API map

OpenAPI `paths` in `docs/api/wincher-openapi.json` omit the `/v1` prefix (server base is `https://api.wincher.com/v1`).

| MCP tool | Wincher endpoint |
|----------|------------------|
| `get_websites` | `GET /v1/websites` |
| `get_keywords` | `GET /v1/websites/{id}/keywords` |
| `get_keyword_rankings` | `GET /v1/websites/{id}/keyword/{kid}/ranking-history` |
| `get_competitor_ranking_summaries` | `GET /v1/websites/{id}/competitors/ranking-summaries` |
| `get_competitor_keyword_positions` | `GET /v1/websites/{id}/competitors/keyword-positions` |
| `get_serps` | `GET /v1/websites/{id}/keywords/{kid}/serps` |
| `get_keyword_groups` | `GET /v1/websites/{id}/groups` |
| `get_bulk_ranking_history` | `POST /v1/websites/{id}/ranking-history` |
| `get_annotations` | `GET /v1/websites/{id}/annotations` |

## New tool checklist

1. Confirm operation in [docs/api/wincher-openapi.json](../../docs/api/wincher-openapi.json) (or refresh via [update-api-spec](../skills/update-api-spec/SKILL.md)). Live docs: https://www.wincher.com/docs/api
2. Add `Tool(...)` in `list_tools()` with schema.
3. Add branch in `call_tool()`; reuse GET helper or POST pattern.
4. Document in `README.md` tool list and add an example in `docs/EXAMPLES.md` if user-facing.
5. Manual smoke test with valid `website_id` / `keyword_id` (see [testing](testing.mdc)).

## Lineage

- **`origin`**: `vmandic/wincher-mcp` — canonical repo and default push target.
- **Early prototype**: `chris-tutt/wincher-mcp-server` — optional selective cherry-picks; do not overwrite vmandic docs/rules without intent.

## Red flags

| Stop | Why |
|------|-----|
| Write/mutate Wincher data via API | Out of scope (read-only product) |
| Caching API keys or responses on disk | Security / staleness |
| Splitting modules without tests or user ask | Premature abstraction |
| Staging host literal in repo or tool errors | Secret leak |
